    {
      "id": "18b4750c-f3ba-8036-b0ed-fdcfe5a60a3b",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors employ a fuzzy approach to create a learner model and a learning activity model. The use of the fuzzy-tree architecture is used to infer relationshios between activities and requirements. Moreover, the authors create a hybrid recommender system using this approach that recommends content. Performance of the algorithm is compared against knowledge-based filtering and collaborative filtering approaches using the MovieLens dataset.",
